title: Independent candidate Ishfaq Ahmed wins PK-89 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Ishfaq Ahmed has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-89 Nowshera-V by securing 30,416 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awami National Party’s Mian Iftikhar Hussain who bagged 15,630 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 49.91 per cent.
